Q: How to configure Hibernate6 default for Timestamp with a nanosecond precision? A: <p>A Hibernate6 solution is to use a custom dialect and override the method <code>getDefaultTimestampPrecision</code> method to return 9:</p>
<pre><code>public class CustomH2Dialect extends H2Dialect {    

    @Override
    public int getDefaultTimestampPrecision() {
        return 9;
    }
}
</code></pre>

Q: Adding multiple function plots to a single figure with subplots - MATLAB A: <p>You could pass back the figure handle to manage this in separate calls. E.g., sample driver:</p>
<pre><code>manipulator1 = [];
manipulator2 = [];
manipulator3 = [];
f = function_plot('data.mat',manipulator1,1);
f = function_plot('data.mat',manipulator2,2,f);
f = function_plot('data.mat',manipulator3,3,f);
</code></pre>
<p>Along with sample plotting function:</p>
<pre><code>function myfigure = function_plot(dataset,manipulator,n,myfigure)

%Manipulates Data

if nargin&lt;4 
    myfigure = figure;
else
    figure(myfigure); 
end

x = -2*pi:0.01:2*pi; % sample data
subplot(3,2,n);
plot(x,sin(x)); grid on % sample plot on left

subplot(3,2,n+3);           
plot(x,cos(x)); grid on % sample plot on right

end
</code></pre>
<p>Produces this:<br />
