Q: Is it possible to export to CSV and have the header contain spaces? A: <p>Here's what I did:</p>
<p>First, clone the CSV export option on your report server (assuming you have access to this).</p>
<p>Keep a backup copy of your rsreportserver.config.  If you change it, you need to restart your reporting services for it to re-read the settings.  If you break it, put the original copy back in and restart services again.</p>
<p>Gist: Update the following section:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;Extension Name=&quot;CSV&quot;&gt;...&lt;/Extension&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>With something like this:</p>
<pre><code>&lt;Extension Name=&quot;CSV&quot; Type=&quot;Microsoft.ReportingServices.Rendering.DataRenderer.CsvReport,Microsoft.ReportingServices.DataRendering&quot;&gt;
&lt;OverrideNames&gt;
    &lt;Name Language=&quot;en-US&quot;&gt;CSV (no header)&lt;/Name&gt;
&lt;/OverrideNames&gt;
&lt;Configuration&gt;
    &lt;DeviceInfo&gt;
        &lt;ExcelMode&gt;False&lt;/ExcelMode&gt;
        &lt;NoHeader&gt;true&lt;/NoHeader&gt;
    &lt;/DeviceInfo&gt;
&lt;/Configuration&gt;
&lt;/Extension&gt;
&lt;Extension Name=&quot;CSVNoHeader&quot; Type=&quot;Microsoft.ReportingServices.Rendering.DataRenderer.CsvReport,Microsoft.ReportingServices.DataRendering&quot;&gt;
&lt;OverrideNames&gt;
    &lt;Name Language=&quot;en-US&quot;&gt;CSV (with header)&lt;/Name&gt;
&lt;/OverrideNames&gt;
&lt;Configuration&gt;
    &lt;DeviceInfo&gt;
        &lt;ExcelMode&gt;False&lt;/ExcelMode&gt;
    &lt;/DeviceInfo&gt;
&lt;/Configuration&gt;
&lt;/Extension&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>this will allow you to have TWO CSV save options, one with headers, one without.</p>
<p>Now you can <em>fake</em> a header by explicitly selecting a first row that has the correct header names like this pseudo query:</p>
<pre><code>SELECT [Column_1] = 'Column 1 header', [Column_2] = 'Column 2 header', etc...
UNION
[Your existing query]
</code></pre>
<p>This gives you a first row that looks like a header.  In your report design DO NOT include a header.  Since your first row has the header names, it looks just like the &quot;right&quot; header.</p>
<p>Finally, run the report, choose the new CSV (no header) option you got from updating rsreportserver.config and restarting reporting services.</p>
<p><a href="https://i.sstatic.net/mLUOnHlD.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.sstatic.net/mLUOnHlD.png" alt="save options for SSRS" title="save options" /></a></p>
<p>Hope this makes sense.  Always be careful, back up files, etc.</p>
